pkt file(download) -> https://github.com/rlcosta177/files/blob/main/radius-telnet-auth.pkt
main reference -> https://ipcisco.com/lesson/cisco-radius-server-configuration-on-packet-tracer/
optional reference -> https://medium.com/@elnurbda/configuring-ssh-telnet-and-tacacs-in-packet-tracer-2e1ebf6f1301

router - 192.168.0.1
radius server - 192.168.0.254
wireless router - 192.168.0.252
dns-server - 192.168.0.254(radius is the dns as well)
switch - 192.168.0.253(vlan 1)

1) create the topology -> Main router(192.168.0.1) / Wireless router connected to the main router / Radius server connected to the main router / switch connecting them all / 

2) configure the radius server to accept the network devices && create users(they will be used to login to the telnet/ssh session

3) configure the device you want to access(router in this case) to allow tellnet/ssh to it self as well as using login local i think
  3.1) line vty 0 4 
       loging local
       transport input telnet/ssh
       login authentication default (optional i think, not sure)
       acccount exec default (optional i think, not sure)
       aaa auth
       exit
       aaa new-model
       radius-server host 192.168.0.254(the AAA server ip) key Passw0rd(probably the same as the one set in the radius server)
       exit
       aaa authentication login default group radius local
       DO WR PLS DONT FORGET DUMBASS
